00:30:35.163 --> 00:30:59.759
He said, 'I've never seen the righteous forsaken or his seed begging bread, regardless of what we see and what's coming in the near future.'I told somebody—I think it was Doc, this guy, his name on the chat was Doc and he was on there while we were watching—'I'm not participating in the economic disaster.

00:30:59.760 --> 00:31:12.535
I refuse to participate in it. For God gives seed to the sower and bread.'I believe He will take care of His own as we have.

00:31:12.536 --> 00:31:19.199
If you're faithful with tithing, if you're faithful in giving, if you've been faithful with little, He'll make you ruler over much.

00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:26.158
And I believe when I saw those people praying over those pots and food came in there, it wasn't just beans.

00:31:26.159 --> 00:31:31.499
It was foods like turkey, mashed potatoes, and gravy—and boom, right there.

00:31:31.500 --> 00:31:41.241
It was like all of a sudden when they prayed, the glory came into the house, filled those pots up with food, and steam was coming off the food.

00:31:41.242 --> 00:31:53.728
I saw the lady in the vision take the lid off this big pot, and there were tons of people in this house, and I saw her take the lid off, and all of a sudden, steam started coming up from this hot food.

00:31:53.729 --> 00:32:00.831
Praise God. And there was nothing in there before, and they had set it like they were having a feast, like a Thanksgiving Day feast.

00:32:00.832 --> 00:32:09.914
Candles were on there. I could see they were anticipating God to show up and show off in their life.

00:32:09.915 --> 00:32:16.265
And God did, because why? Because that's the kind of God we serve.

00:32:16.266 --> 00:32:21.075
In the middle of the night, I remember hearing... Was it George Mueller?

00:32:21.076 --> 00:32:25.541
No, not George Mueller. But there was another one I remember hearing: it was Oral Roberts.

00:32:25.542 --> 00:32:42.662
And Oral Roberts said their papa was out preaching, and there was no food in the house, and the people at the church didn't take care of them very much.

00:32:42.663 --> 00:32:48.819
They didn't have any food, and they were really, really hungry. I'm talking really hungry.

00:32:48.820 --> 00:32:57.652
And his brother was mouthing off to Oral on the way home, saying, 'God doesn't take care of us,'and just popping off.

00:32:57.653 --> 00:33:02.059
He said, 'Shut up, or I'm going to hit you in the head,'basically, because God is going to take care of us.

00:33:02.060 --> 00:33:08.722
And so they got all the way home, and he was bickering back and forth, him and his brother, because they didn't have anything to eat.

00:33:08.723 --> 00:33:13.038
And all of a sudden, Mama—because Mama said, 'I'm not going to beg for money.

00:33:13.039 --> 00:33:19.089
We're not going to do anything'—well, they got invited over to the neighbor's house, and she had all that food set out, remember?

00:33:19.090 --> 00:33:27.367
And they saw them eating the food, and Mama said, 'No, we're fine.'And he was thinking, 'No, we're not!

00:33:27.368 --> 00:33:35.794
We're starving!'They sat there and watched them because they said, 'Do you want to eat some of this?'and she said, 'No, we're okay.

00:33:35.795 --> 00:33:48.091
We're going to be just fine. God's going to take care of us.'So they went home, and what happened? Something hit their door.

00:33:48.092 --> 00:33:55.384
Somebody knocked on their door, and when they opened the door, there was all this food—all these groceries.

00:33:55.385 --> 00:34:06.558
There was a full turkey, gravy, biscuits—and it was at night.

00:34:06.559 --> 00:34:13.358
It was at night, and he said Mom went in there, and they were so hungry she made a big feast.

00:34:13.359 --> 00:34:19.559
She goes, 'Oral, go get the flour.'She got a big sack of flour, she got the eggs, and she said, 'Oral, go get the stuff out there.

00:34:19.560 --> 00:34:23.329
I'm going to make something to eat.'So they made it at night.

00:34:23.330 --> 00:34:27.199
They had a huge feast of biscuits and gravy, and they went to bed.

00:34:27.200 --> 00:34:32.637
And he told his little brother, 'I told you God would provide for us.

00:34:32.638 --> 00:34:39.838
I told you God would provide for us.'And every time I hear that, I say, 'He'll do it again and again.

00:34:39.839 --> 00:34:45.941
He'll do it again and again if you believe Him.'I'm a believing believer. I'm not a doubter.

00:34:45.942 --> 00:34:59.565
And I tell you these stories of what God is doing to inspire you to believe for your family in the days ahead, to say, 'Hey, I'm not going to participate in this.'I know what the Lord has told me is coming, ladies and gentlemen.

00:34:59.566 --> 00:35:09.322
And it will be times like we've never seen before because back then in the 1930s, people at least knew how to grow a garden.

00:35:09.323 --> 00:35:16.431
Now they don't even know how to grow some flowers, let alone a garden. It's serious.

00:35:16.432 --> 00:35:21.546
And so that's what the Lord was showing me: people don't even know how to hunt. What would you do if you shot an animal?

00:35:21.547 --> 00:35:25.519
They don't know how to even gut an animal, field dress it, and get it cleaned up.

00:35:25.520 --> 00:35:30.163
They wouldn't know what to do. That's what I'm saying. There's a lot of people who are not educated.

00:35:30.164 --> 00:35:33.265
They know a lot about computers, but they don't know about how to live.

00:35:33.266 --> 00:35:39.407
They know how to go down to McDonald's and tell them, 'I want a Happy Meal,'but they don't know how to do this.

00:35:39.408 --> 00:35:50.196
And I've seen very challenging days in the near future when this plague comes and these times come. There are hard times I've seen coming. Now, can we pray?

00:35:50.197 --> 00:36:00.870
People say that's the main thing: 'Can we pray this away?'I know that God can lessen anything, but there are parts of it...

00:36:00.871 --> 00:36:10.754
we don't want to go through hard times because we want to pass it on to the next person. But what will shake the world to bring in the harvest?

00:36:10.755 --> 00:36:23.094
That's why I said that whenever Jesus was getting ready to die on the cross, he said, 'Not my will, but yours be done.'It's not always comfortable for my flesh to go through something sometimes.

00:36:23.095 --> 00:36:26.887
Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

00:36:26.888 --> 00:36:34.719
He didn't say you wouldn't walk through the valley. Sometimes you walk through the valley, but we don't have to fear it.

00:36:34.720 --> 00:36:43.350
Sometimes we go through, you know, 'A thousand shall fall at our side, ten thousand at our right hand.'That means there are people dying around you.

00:36:43.351 --> 00:36:50.026
Regardless if a thousand fell around you or ten thousand at your right hand, something's going on for that to be happening.

00:36:50.027 --> 00:36:53.753
That means something was happening. Do you understand? Ten thousand, am I right?

00:36:53.754 --> 00:37:05.145
Ten thousand. I mean, seriously, that's a lot of folks. That's 11,000 people. That's a bad day. But it won't come nigh me.

00:37:05.146 --> 00:37:13.676
'Only with thine eyes shalt thou behold and see the reward of the wicked.'Father, I thank you, Lord, for Psalm 91.

00:37:13.677 --> 00:37:23.519
